class psexecinfo.PsexecShellVariables(_conn: pypsexec.client.Client, _executable: str, _actual_work_dir: str = 'C:\\Windows\\System32', _possible_work_dir: str = 'C:\\Windows\\System32', _shell_command: Optional[str] = None)¶

[Class to group all the information to perform psexec]

Parameters

  • _conn (Client) – [ Object with the current psexec connection ]

  • _executable (str) – [ Program that will be executed Ej: cmd.exe or powershell.exe ]

  • _actual_work_dir (str, optional) – [ Current directory to run executables]. Defaults to “C:WindowsSystem32”.

  • _possible_work_dir (str, optional) – [ Directory to change in case of perform cd ]. Defaults to “C:WindowsSystem32”.

  • _shell_command (str , optional) – [ Command run in cmd.exe or powershell.exe]. Defaults to None.
